I rarely accept current production, customs, or very common guns on trade. If you have a quality modern firearm you seldom see in most Gun Shops priced with my resale in mind I will probably be interested in it. Email me a very detailed description of your firearm or if you have more than one email a list with a detailed description and pricing or an idea of how much you need to get out of your trade or trades. This means the payment you send must clear our bank first, this may take up to 4 business days depending on your payment form. Hardware is included as well as extra screws and bushings. The IWB mounts are steel spring clips. The back is lined and double stitched. I have two Kydex shells. One shell is for just the gun. One shell is for the gun with the light attached. Both mount to the leather back plate. This is an extremely comfortable and adaptable holster. Ammo:I am including 5 boxes (250 rounds) of factory sealed Eagle brand ammo for range use. Each box is unopened. I would either like accessories and ammo to even the trade, or cash to make up the difference, maybe a combination of both. I will also look at higher end 1911's as even trade. This is to become a dedicated carry gun, so entry to mid level is preferred. Not looking for a 9mm 1911 unless it's the new TCM with cash or accessories. All trades acknowledged, but I'm just really looking for what's listed. Thanks in advance for time and consideration. Happy Holidays to all and be safe. Again, thank you and have a good day. Also, I realize the holidays are upon us and money is allocated elsewhere. title: For Sale/Trade:  LaRue LT110 QD Mount
postcontent:
Awesome co-witness mount for eotech with QD. Lighty used with 1 optic on 1 rifle and sat in the safe. Very SOLID mount!
Details from the LarRue site: http://www.larue.com/larue-tactical-eotech-qd-mount-lt-110
 
Converts low-profile EOTechs to lower 1/3 cowitness, and provides a better cheekweld too.
The LT110 is another mount designed "by request". The LT110 raises the EOTech by .275". This extra height sticks the irons low in the EOTech's window...you can still see the irons if push-comes-to-shove.
 
The response has been outstanding. The extra height is just what the EO has been needing. The design had room for a piece-of-picatinny on the back, so we put it there and now you can mount a PVS-14 or Aimpoint 3X Magnifier in perfect co-witness.
 
Like all LaRue mounts, it is precision-machined out of bar-stock aluminum and matt black anodized to provide a durable non-reflective surface finish. The locking LaRue Speed Lever provides outstanding return to zero; the optic can be removed, and replaced, without loss of zero. Guaranteed.
 
Comes complete with locking lever instruction card and 1 LT2005-B box wrench.
 
NOTE: The LT110 EOTech Mount will work correctly with 511, 512, 551, 552, XPS-2, XPS-3 and similar models. It will NOT work with the EXPS2 or EXPS3, it also will NOT work with 516, 517, 553 or 557 models (or any EOTech with a built-in riser). The LT110 is not compatible with an EOLAD installed.
 
The LT-133 (PVS-14 Mount) and LT-602-1 (fixed Aimpoint 3X Magnifier Mount) attach on the rear of the LT-110 and correctly line-up with the LT-110-mounted 511, 512, 551, 552, XPS 2, XPS 3 and similar models. The LT-649 "Tall" Pivot Mount (with Aimpoint 3X magnifier), mounted on the receiver rail will work on all models, but may interfere with rear sights.

title: For Sale:  STEYR S40-A1, 10rd, .40 S & F'ing W
postcontent: If you haven't heard of Steyr handguns, consider yourself put on notice! This firearm is incredible. This is the Glock slayer. This weapon has seen less than 100 rounds down the pipe. Perfect 5 Star review on Buds. A little about this fine weapon, worth the read, because who doesn't like gun porn?The size and weight of the S40-A1 is similar to other popular compact striker-fired .40 S&W pistols on the market today. However, its sleek lines, generous trigger guard, and ergonomic grip configuration make it stand out from the crowd. The steel slide is treated with a surface-hardening Tenifer finish and is topped with Steyr's proprietary metallic triangle/trapezoid sight system. The sights are possibly the most remarkable part of this weapon. Incredible smooth and quick target aquisition. The double-action-only trigger is fitted with a safety system, not unlike the Glock Safe-Action trigger, that Steyr calls a Reset Action Trigger. It tipped the digital trigger gauge at 5 lbs. 5 ozs. The short, smooth, crisp trigger stroke feels lighter and easier to operate than the digital gauge indicates. The fit and finish of the steel and polymer components was excellent and the pistol was free of the mysterious internal rattles that show up in some modern pistols when given a shake.You will not find a better weapon for this price point.
